President Biden addressed the nation from the National Institutes of Health (NIH) in Bethesda, Maryland, to announce his action plan to combat COVID-19 during the winter months. The plan focuses on expanding the nationwide booster campaign, launching new family vaccination clinics, making free at-home tests more available, increasing surge response teams, and accelerating efforts to vaccinate the rest of the world. President Biden emphasized the importance of vaccination, booster shots, and testing in order to protect the population and keep schools and businesses open. He also mentioned the need for international travel rules and tighter testing requirements for inbound travelers. The President expressed confidence in the country's ability to fight the Omicron variant and highlighted the progress made in job creation and economic growth despite the ongoing pandemic. He assured that the government is prepared to prevent a shutdown and that there is a plan in place to avoid any disruptions.